---
import fs from 'node:fs';
import path from 'node:path';
import { Code } from 'astro:components';
import Doc from '../layouts/Doc.astro';
import SchemaFields from '../components/SchemaFields.astro';

// Single-sourced from the schema: field rows are generated, so this page
// cannot drift from the contract it documents.
const schemaRaw = fs.readFileSync(path.resolve(process.cwd(), '../../schemas/context-manifest.schema.json'), 'utf-8');
const schema = JSON.parse(schemaRaw);
// A manifest that exercises every field; verified against the schema above.
const exampleRaw = fs.readFileSync(path.resolve(process.cwd(), 'src/data/manifest-complete.json'), 'utf-8');
---

<Doc title="The manifest (leji.json) · Leji">
   <h1>The manifest: <code>leji.json</code></h1>
   <p class="sp-lede">{schema.description}</p>

   <p>
      The manifest is the only fixed filename in Leji: the one file tooling can always expect at the repository root.
      Field rows are generated from
      <a href="/schemas/context-manifest/">the schema</a>, so the page and the contract cannot disagree. Required fields
      carry the gold mark.
   </p>

   <h2>Fields</h2>
   <SchemaFields schema={schema} />

   <h2>A complete example</h2>
   <p>
      This complete manifest validates against the schema and exercises every field: a federated, organization-wide
      context layer that mounts a sibling. Most context layers use only the subset they need; this one uses all of them.
   </p>
   <div class="manifest-example">
      <Code code={exampleRaw.trimEnd()} lang="json" theme="night-owl" wrap />
   </div>

   <p>
      See <a href="/spec/machine-readable-surface/">the machine-readable surface</a> for how the manifest relates to the index,
      changelog, and profiles, and
      <a href="/spec/versioning/">versioning</a> for the <code>leji</code> spec-line key.
   </p>
</Doc>

<style>
   .manifest-example :global(.astro-code) {
      background: var(--blue-deep) !important;
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 1.2rem 1.4rem;
      font-size: var(--code-fz);
      line-height: 1.6;
   }
</style>
